The Prime Minister does not rule out calling early elections by the end of the year.
Immediately after the Liberal Party (Parti libéral) congress, Jean Charest moved to Jean-Talon, Quebec, where the new Minister of Health, Yves Bolduc (left), is running in today's by-election.
'Drawing the line of our last great northern frontier': this is the long-term ambition that Jean Charest presented in a visually compelling way yesterday at the conclusion of the Quebec Liberal Party congress in Lévis, without giving details.
During his speech, pictures were projected behind his back in a kind of picture mill.
