Today is the release of Open Office.org 3.0, an open source personal development suite that aims to reach more and more users, from the home to the office, from professionals to public administration, as a free alternative to the more common Microsoft Office.
After about a year of volunteer work, controlled by SUN Microsystems, the new Open Office is being released to the general public with various new features: the welcome screen and the revised and improved opening window are being supplemented by more substantial features such as compatibility for the Apple Mac OS X operating system and support for the new ODF (Open Document Format) 1.2, the latest ISO standard.
