Open Office consists of five main models: Writer, for writing video replacing Word; Calc is a spreadsheet processor that is aiming to replace Excel; Impress for PowerPoint-like presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the more famous Access, is a program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, finally, is a graphical model.
